{
  "id": 45627,
  "kuerzel": "M_ElSolT",
  "bezeichnung": "Electrical Solar Technology",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>&nbsp;Students can explain how a solar cell works, how a solar module is constructed, and calculate its parameters. They can explain the key considerations when dimensioning photovoltaic systems and design a simple photovoltaic system. They can describe battery storage systems, highlighting their advantages and disadvantages, and explain how to integrate them into the system for intermediate storage, as well as perform basic sizing calculations. Students can calculate the yield of photovoltaic systems and place it in the energy system. They can name the costs of photovoltaic systems and current market developments.&nbsp;</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "keine Note oder Wertung",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "aktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 45628,
      "kuerzel": "PhoWiWaTec",
      "bezeichnung": "Photovoltaics und battery storage",
      "lernziele": "siehe Modulbeschreibung",
      "planinhalt": "<p><strong>Photovoltaics and battery storage</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The sun as a source of irradiation</li>\n<li>Function of a solar cell: photovoltaic effect, p-n junction, efficiency</li>\n<li>From the solar cell to the solar module</li>\n<li>Characteristic curves of solar cells and modules with the influence of irradiation and temperature</li>\n<li>Shading, mismatch, and the function of bypass diodes&nbsp;</li>\n<li>PV systems and their components (inverters, mounting system)</li>\n<li>Dimensioning and yield of PV systems</li>\n<li>Battery storage for PV systems</li>\n<li>Design of PV systems with battery storage</li>\n<li>Grid-connected and off-grid PV systems</li>\n<li>PV in the power grid, interaction of power generation and consumption</li>\n<li>Measurement methods and fault detection</li>\n<li>Costs, economics, and life cycle assessment</li>\n<li>PV market, potential and development trends&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
